Date: Mon, 19 Jun 2017 15:10:32 +0800
Subject: [PATCH] v4l: vsp1: fixed build error in vsp1_pipeline_stopped

It will fixed build error as follow:
include/linux/spinlock_rt.h:136:2: error: expected expression before 'do'
do {      \

Signed-off-by: zou cao <cao.zou@windriver.com>
---
 drivers/media/platform/vsp1/vsp1_pipe.c |    2 +-
 1 files changed, 1 insertions(+), 1 deletions(-)

diff --git a/drivers/media/platform/vsp1/vsp1_pipe.c b/drivers/media/platform/vsp1/vsp1_pipe.c
index d1a347f..a90d74e 100644
--- a/drivers/media/platform/vsp1/vsp1_pipe.c
+++ b/drivers/media/platform/vsp1/vsp1_pipe.c
@@ -199,7 +199,7 @@ bool vsp1_pipeline_stopped(struct vsp1_pipeline *pipe)
 	bool stopped;
 
 	spin_lock_irqsave(&pipe->irqlock, flags);
-	stopped = pipe->state == VSP1_PIPELINE_STOPPED,
+	stopped = pipe->state == VSP1_PIPELINE_STOPPED;
 	spin_unlock_irqrestore(&pipe->irqlock, flags);
 
 	return stopped;
